WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.940 --> 00:00:03.940
ALAN SEALES: The winner of five
2015 Tony awards, including

00:00:03.940 --> 00:00:05.630
best musical, "Fun
Home" is based

00:00:05.630 --> 00:00:08.870
on Alison Bechdel's best-selling
memoir of the same name.

00:00:08.870 --> 00:00:10.810
This groundbreaking
production introduces us

00:00:10.810 --> 00:00:13.430
to the character of
Alison, and herself

00:00:13.430 --> 00:00:15.600
at three different
ages, revealing memories

00:00:15.600 --> 00:00:18.630
of her uniquely dysfunctional
family that connect her

00:00:18.630 --> 00:00:20.020
in surprising new ways.

00:00:20.020 --> 00:00:21.920
And here to perform
with us today, please

00:00:21.920 --> 00:00:24.430
welcome all three Alisons--
Gabriella Pizzolo,

00:00:24.430 --> 00:00:26.510
Emily Skeggs, and Beth Malone.

00:00:26.510 --> 00:00:28.162
[APPLAUSE]

00:00:33.540 --> 00:00:34.960
EMILY SKEGGS: Hi, Google.

00:00:34.960 --> 00:00:36.450
It's good to be here today.

00:00:36.450 --> 00:00:38.450
So I'm going to sing a
song from the show called

00:00:38.450 --> 00:00:39.660
"Changing My Major."

00:00:39.660 --> 00:00:43.470
It's the moment in the show
where the college-age Alison

00:00:43.470 --> 00:00:46.710
has woken up and
she has just slept

00:00:46.710 --> 00:00:48.536
with a woman for the first time.

00:00:48.536 --> 00:00:50.202
[MUSIC - FUN HOME, "CHANGING MY
 MAJOR"]

00:00:57.372 --> 00:05:03.762
[SINGING "CHANGING MY MAJOR"]

00:05:03.762 --> 00:05:06.738
[APPLAUSE]

00:05:14.178 --> 00:05:15.680
GABRIELLA PIZZOLO: Hi.

00:05:15.680 --> 00:05:20.140
There's a moment in "Fun
Home" when Alison and her dad

00:05:20.140 --> 00:05:26.270
are in a diner, and Alison's
dad says, go find the waitress.

00:05:26.270 --> 00:05:28.890
And on Alison's way
to find the waitress,

00:05:28.890 --> 00:05:33.576
she sees a woman who
she identifies with.

00:05:33.576 --> 00:05:36.066
[MUSIC - FUN HOME, "RING OF
 KEYS"]

00:05:41.046 --> 00:08:21.790
[SINGING "RING OF KEYS"]

00:08:21.790 --> 00:08:24.744
[APPLAUSE]

00:08:33.570 --> 00:08:34.289
BETH MALONE: Hi.

00:08:34.289 --> 00:08:37.630
I am them grown
up, older, and I'm

00:08:37.630 --> 00:08:41.110
writing a book about those
moments in my life now.

00:08:41.110 --> 00:08:45.750
And so as I investigate
my past, the memories

00:08:45.750 --> 00:08:47.810
sort of become all-encompassing.

00:08:47.810 --> 00:08:53.510
And this song takes place
in a car with my father

00:08:53.510 --> 00:08:55.210
when I'm Emily's age.

00:08:55.210 --> 00:08:57.620
But I have remembered
it so fully,

00:08:57.620 --> 00:09:04.450
and it has sort of put me in the
present in the car with my dad

00:09:04.450 --> 00:09:05.919
at this age.

